# Docs Markdown Conventions

## Figures

When including figures in markdown files under `docs/`:

- **Width:** Display images at **600px** wide only.
- **Aspect ratio:** Preserve aspect ratio (height scales automatically).

Use HTML `<img>` with explicit width and auto height. Do **not** use plain markdown image syntax `![](path)` for figures, because it does not control size.

**Format:**

```html
<img src="figures/filename.ext" alt="Descriptive alt text" width="600" style="height: auto;" />
```

**Example:**

```html
<img src="figures/pct_of_mean_by_regime_03012026.png" alt="Marginal effect as % of mean closure rate by period" width="600" style="height: auto;" />
```

- `width="600"` sets display width to 600px.
- `style="height: auto;"` keeps the image proportional.

Apply this to every figure reference you add or edit in `docs/**/*.md`.

