## AI-written explanations

When you add **interpretive or explanatory paragraphs** in `docs/` that **interpret generated results** (e.g. reconciling regression results with other findings, explaining why a coefficient might be large or change over time, discussing economic mechanisms, or drafting narrative about what the results mean):

1. **Put the content in a box** (bordered block so it is visually distinct).
2. **Prefix the first line with "AI WRITTEN:"** and style that label in red (see example below).

**When it applies:** Only when the text **interprets** already-generated results—i.e. explains what coefficients or patterns mean, offers possible mechanisms, reconciles different results, or draws implications. It does **not** apply to:

- **Sample construction** (how the sample was built, which units or years are included, restrictions).
- **Regression specification** (which variables, fixed effects, controls, or standard errors are used).
- **Design or methodology** (what the outcome variable is, how treatment is defined, identification logic).
- **Source citations**, table captions, or verbatim quotes from papers or code.

Those are factual/descriptive and do not need the AI WRITTEN box. Reserve the box for **interpretation of results** (e.g. “a possible explanation is…”, “this reconciles with…”, “the coefficient is larger because…”).

**Format:** Use the shared CSS classes from `docs/css/site.css` (included by `default.html`). Do **not** duplicate these styles inline. Use class-based markup:

```html
<div class="ai-written-box">
<p><strong class="ai-written-label">AI WRITTEN:</strong> Your explanatory or interpretive text here. For example: the positive coefficient on closures is larger in later subperiods, while deposit reallocation results show incumbents no longer gain—a possible explanation is that closing banks retain deposits at remaining branches…</p>
</div>
```

- **Box:** Use `class="ai-written-box"` on the wrapper `div` (styles: border, padding, margin).
- **Red label:** Use `class="ai-written-label"` on the **AI WRITTEN:** element (e.g. `<strong class="ai-written-label">AI WRITTEN:</strong>`).
- **Scope:** Use this only when you are **interpreting generated results** (coefficients, patterns, mechanisms, reconciliation). Do not use it for methodology, sample construction, regression specification, design description, verbatim quotes, table captions, or source citations.

