## Shared CSS classes (do not duplicate inline)

Styles for callout and AI-written boxes live in **`docs/css/site.css`** and are included by `docs/_layouts/default.html`. When adding or editing content in `docs/**/*.md`, use these **classes** instead of inline `style="..."` so styles stay consistent and in one place.

| Class | Use for | Markup |
|-------|--------|--------|
| `ai-written-box` | Wrapper for AI-written interpretation paragraphs | `<div class="ai-written-box">` |
| `ai-written-label` | Red "AI WRITTEN:" prefix inside the box | `<strong class="ai-written-label">AI WRITTEN:</strong>` |
| `callout-addressed` | Green "Addressed" / response callouts (e.g. referee comment responses) | `<div class="callout-addressed">` |

**Callout-addressed example** (e.g. in response-plan or similar):

```html
<div class="callout-addressed">
**✓ Addressed.** Your response text here…
</div>
```

Do **not** copy the equivalent inline styles into markdown; use the class so future changes to `site.css` apply everywhere.

